<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Aladain:
[B]Absolutely amazing.  I don't think I could have written it better.

I run a guild on Thlouxe Paells.  Those of you there have no doubt heard of us - The Avengers Federation.  We also have divisions on Erollisi Marr, The Nameless, and Sol Ro.  I do not run those divisions, but we all work in the same, I just take different leadership visions of the guild than the others (which is fine) - But my thoughts I'm going to post below are mine and reflect the AF on Thlouxe Paells, not necessarily the other divisions.  (Just needed to say that!)

My guild consists of a few of us in our 50s, a lot in the 40s, and many others from level 4 to the 30s.  Whether you are level 4 or level 60, you're a human being sitting on a chair playing a game.  What defines honor and moral is respect to the person?  I get asked often "Damn aladain, you need some better stuff".  Whats that mean?  Anyone thats been in a group with me knows that not only am I a damn damn damn good cleric, but I am a VERY respectful person, and bring a lot of charming personality to the groups I'm in.  How do I improve on that with better loot?   I want people to like me, and respect me for me, not what I've got on my back.

In my guild, we too raid "here and there" but its not the reason we're around.  We exist because of the people in the guild.  We exist to make ourselves, AND others happy to be around good people.  If anyone in my guild gets too self-centered about loot, or causes a "Poor-taste" argument about loot, they are not welcome.  Loot is loot, and disagreements are fine, but as long as its reasonable.  If someone wants to leave us because "I can't do XXX with you guys" so be it.  They are good people, yes, but I don't want people in my guild that are not happy.  If someone is sad because we can't up and go kill Trakanon, then our guild isn't for them.

As of current, I have a lot of 50+ players in the AF (I think 7-8 which to me at least, it a lot).  But, instead of being in a big guild, OR guild "Alliances" - we have a large number of people - numbering up to 100-120.  They are in different small guilds.  Some are in no guilds.  And we're doing planes fine.  We'll move to harder stuff later as well.  We want to give everyone a chance to get nice stuff, but its not for "getting nice stuff" - its for the experence to do it with GOOD people.  With low low (Character) self-esteem some people have in their equipment - I have little sympathy for them.  Want to know how to get sympathy from me?  DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT.  Do what Spiritlance, Chronicus and Waggs do on Thlouxe Paells (BIG BIG Kudos to those 3).  Get these other people together, and make it happen.  Get off your ass and make it happen.  Waggs gets beat to death on experence (He has lost almost all of 53 on these raids, and I think hes ate 1 res).  The guy doesnt care, though, hes making others happy, and that satisfies him.

Powergamers will always have a place, and I too respect them - I do not respect someone being a "better person" because they dont have a_uber_item01.

Aladain[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
